column3: I loved this video, Lael absolute inspiration, the editing, the incredible sequence at minute 10:54, what a great cinematography!!!

I can attest to the fact the Alaskans are willing to help out others:  I rode to AK back in 1992 up from Los Angeles.  I hit a couple of destinations such as Homer, Valdez, etc.  Awesome place.  Once I made it to Fairbanks, I decided to go up to Prudhoe Bay.  Unfortunately I ended up with a terrible tooth ache in the middle of nowhere, somewhere south of the Yukon.  A local gave me a ride all the way back to Fairbanks.  It was on his way; nevertheless he helped out a stranger in need.
